description:
Fixer+Upper - Season 5, Episode 4




Historic Tudor-Style Home for a New Family

Chip and Joanna Gaines take on a historical project for Courtney and Joey Scrivano, who are ready to upgrade from their modest loft to a house where they can raise their new baby. Built in 1927, their Tudor-style home is outdated, has little functionality, and lacks a true master suite. With a renovation budget of $200,000, Chip and Jo get to work preserving the home's historic charm while making sure it meets the needs of this new modern family.




Original Air Date: 12-Dec-2017
